description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;30 Hours per week (Fixed term for 12 months)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the 30 hour post of ward clerk on Victoria ward at the Friary Hospital Richmond North Yorkshire. The post holder will work Monday-Friday .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated, enthusiastic, confident person who can demonstrate excellent communication skills. They must have good organisational skills and an ability to work on his/her own initiative and be a good team player.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must be computer literate and experience of clerical duties and filing is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will work closely with the multi-disciplinary team and they will have direct contact with patients, relatives and other members of the public. They will have reception duties and will be able to handle public enquiries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note this vacancy will close when we receive sufficient completed applications.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lorraine Bone (Ward manager)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email: Lorrainebone@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel: 01742 822109&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OR &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Karen Frankland (Ward Sister)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
